EmacsConf is being held in London, here's a few useful links:

* [[http://www.forward.co.uk/contact|ForwardGroup - where it's being held]]
* https://www.heathrowconnect.com/index.asp?SID={65C76CDC-2EFD-4589-A223-809157EAA164} - Heathrow Connect - cheaper arrival
* [[https://www.heathrowexpress.com/timetable-schedule|Heathrow Express]] - more expensive arrival, about Â£20
* [[http://tfl.gov.uk|Transport for London]] - getting around in London government website
** The tube is pretty famous for making it easy to get about
** [[http://www.tfl.gov.uk/assets/downloads/standard-tube-map.pdf|the Tube Map (pdf)]]
** Buses are good too because you get to do some sightseeing on the way
** Get yourself an [[http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oyster_card|Oyster Card]]. London public transport without one is very expensive.
** [[http://www.tfl.gov.uk/gettingaround/maps/buses/pdf/central-london-bus-map.pdf|central London Bus map (pdf)]]
** [[http://www.tfl.gov.uk/gettingaround/maps/buses/|Bus route page]]

If you're not scared of London traffic you can also try the [[http://www.tfl.gov.uk/roadusers/cycling/15025.aspx Boris Bikes]].
The nearest drop off/pick up point for the conference is on [[https://maps.google.co.uk/maps/ms?msid=211851488558446065226.0004b927b3272e57943ac&msa=0&ll=51.536886,-0.134153&spn=0.014895,0.042272 Royal College Street]] which is a 5 minute ride from Kings Cross station.
